NAME
    passwd - change user password

SYNOPSIS
    passwd <newpassword>
    passwd <username> <newpassword>
    echo "newpassword" | passwd

DESCRIPTION
    Changes the password for a user account.

    Non-root users can only change their own password.
    Root users can change any user's password.

    Passwords are stored using Argon2id hashing.
    Minimum password length is 4 characters.

ARGUMENTS
    newpassword
            The new password

    username
            Target user whose password to change (root only)

SECURITY
    To avoid passwords appearing in command history, pipe the
    password via stdin:

        echo "mysecretpass" | passwd
        echo "mysecretpass" | passwd bob

EXAMPLES
    passwd newpass123
        Change your own password

    passwd bob newpass123
        Change bob's password (root only)

    echo "secretpass" | passwd
        Change password without it appearing in history

EXIT STATUS
    0   Password changed successfully
    1   Error (permission denied, user not found, etc.)

SEE ALSO
    whoami, env
